Test: eval

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

2020-07-08

Source: vignettes/tests/test_eval.Rmd
test_eval.Rmd
library(testthat)
library(jeksterslabRboot)
context("Test eval.")
result <- ci_eval(
  ci = c(1, 3),
  thetahat = 2,
  theta = 2
)
#> Length of label is incompatible. Defaulting to label = 1:(length(ci)/2).

testthat

Confidence interval contain zero.

test_that("TRUE", {
  expect_true(
    zero_hit(
      lo = -1,
      up = 1
    ),
    theta_hit(
      lo = -1,
      theta = 0,
      up = 1
    )
  )
})

Confidence interval does not contain zero.

test_that("FALSE", {
  expect_false(
    zero_hit(
      lo = 1,
      up = 2
    ),
    theta_hit(
      lo = 1,
      theta = 0,
      up = 2
    )
  )
})
test_that("1", {
  expect_equal(
    len(
      lo = 1,
      up = 2
    ),
    shape(
      lo = -1,
      thetahat = 0,
      up = 1
    ),
    1
  )
})

ci_eval

test_that("zero_hit", {
  expect_false(
    as.logical(result[1])
  )
})
test_that("theta_hit", {
  expect_true(
    as.logical(result[2])
  )
})
test_that("len", {
  expect_equivalent(
    result[3],
    2
  )
})
test_that("shape", {
  expect_equivalent(
    result[4],
    1
  )
})
test_that("message", {
  expect_message(
    ci_eval(
      ci = c(0, 1, 2, 3),
      thetahat = 2,
      theta = 2,
      label = "wrong length"
    )
  )
})
test_that("error", {
  expect_error(
    ci_eval(
      ci = 1,
      thetahat = 2,
      theta = 2
    )
  )
})
